  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Roughly chop/slice the tomatoes, season with salt and put in a sieve over a bowl to catch the juice. For the dressing, peel the garlic, finely chop the pickled jalapeños."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the garlic to a pestle and mortar (if you don't have one use a blender or just finely chop everything), smash the garlic then add the anchovies, smooshing them into a paste."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add the jalapeños and keep smooshing until it comes together, then add the mayo and the lemon zest before juicing in half of the lemon – taste and adjust with the remaining lemon juice if needed. Grate in the Parmesan. Give it a good season with some black pepper and taste again. If you think it needs salt, add it."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Peel the courgette into ribbons and finely slice the fresh jalapeño. Arrange the tomatoes and courgette ribbons on a serving platter. Drizzle with the dressing, scatter with basil, crunchy corn and Parmesan shavings."
    }
  ],
